South African mining output increased for the first time in nine months in July as coal and iron ore production surged. Mining production rose 2.4% from a year earlier compared with a revised 4.1% decline in June, Pretoria-based Statistics South Africa said in a report on its website Thursday. The median estimate of five economists in a Bloomberg survey was for a 1% increase. Key insights - With assistance fromÂ Simbarashe Gumbo. 